Example data report for LPD

What we need from LPD:

Basic spreadsheet / data frame format with one row for each traffic stop is best. Any file type is fine (Excel, CSV, plaintext, Google Sheets, others too). Weve randomly generated 50,000 rows of fake data, just showing the first 10:

date name gender race age outcome
2020-01-01 (redacted) man Unknown under 25 verbal warning
2020-01-01 (redacted) man Unknown 35 - 50 ticket
2020-01-01 (redacted) man White 35 - 50 verbal warning
2020-01-01 (redacted) man White 35 - 50 verbal warning
2020-01-01 (redacted) man Asian 35 - 50 verbal warning
2020-01-01 (redacted) man White 35 - 50 written warning
2020-01-01 (redacted) man White under 25 verbal warning
2020-01-01 (redacted) woman White under 25 verbal warning
2020-01-01 (redacted) man Black 35 - 50 verbal warning
2020-01-01 (redacted) man Unknown 26 - 35 ticket

etc.

What we can make with this data:

We can look at outcomes for any subgroups we want and compare them.

We can also look at outcomes over time to track improvements/trends. Again, this is fake data - the real data probably has some interesting seasonal patterns.

Other ways we could break down the data:

  • By age (probably age category, to preserve anonymity)
  • By reason for stop (speeding, suspicion, mechanical)
  • ?? others ?
